Package fr.insa.rennes.info.chemical.backend

Interface Summary
Builder<T> A basic interface describing the builder design pattern used within the library.
BuilderIndexProvider An interface specifying an index provider builder.
BuilderSubIndexProviderSolution An interface specifying a builder for a SubIndexProviderSolution.
IncrementStrategy This interface describes an increment strategy of an index provider.
SubIndexProvider This interface describes the behavior of a sub index provider, used by a IndexProvider.
SubSolutionReactivesAccessor This interface provides an access to reactives within an inner solution.
 

Class Summary
BuilderIndexProviderImpl Standard implementation of BuilderIndexProvider.
BuilderSubIndexProviderSolutionImpl Standard implementation of BuilderSubIndexProviderSolution.
ChemicalThread This class executes a reaction, it uses a reaction rule object and its ReactionRule.computeSelect() and ReactionRule.computeResult() functions to process to reactions.
IndexProvider This class represents an index counter on set of reactives of a given solution.
OrderedIncrementStrategy This class implements an ordered strategy iteration on reactives: the elements are selected in order of appearance in the the solution.
Pair<A,B> This class represents a simple pair of objects.
RandomIncrementStrategy This class implements an random strategy iteration on reactives: the elements are randomly selected in order to simulate the non-determinism of a chemical reaction.
Solution Central class of the library.
SubIndexProviderElement This class represents a sub index provider over a simple element.
SubIndexProviderSolution This class represents a specific case of IndexProviderElement.
SubSolution<T extends SubSolutionReactivesAccessor> This class implements SubSolutionReactivesAccessor and is part of a recursive structure constructed from SubSolution and SubSolutionElements objects.
SubSolutionElements This class implements SubSolutionReactivesAccessor, and is actually the bottom of the recursive structure formed with an interlocking of SubSolution instances.
Triple<A,B,C> This class represents a simple triplet of objects.
Utils Utility class, used in all the project.
 

Enum Summary
Solution.Strategy Different strategies available for reactive selection sequence.
 

Exception Summary
ChemicalException ChemicalException is an exception that indicates an error inherent to the chemical library.
